      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De virtute</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e112">Non res eadem semper est virtus, quia per
              momenta temporum saepe merita mutantur actionum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e127">Plerumque virtus cum indiscrete tenetur,
              amittitur; cum discrete intermittitur, plus tenetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e134">Augustinus,
              <title>de Civitate Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e142"
              source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l19-d1e3187">Virtutes, quas sibi habere mens
              videtur, per quas imperat corpori et vitiis, ad quodlibet adipiscendum vel tenendum,
              nisi ad Deum retulerit, etiam ipsae vitia sunt potius, quam virtutes.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e149">Augustinus,
              <title>de Libero Arbitrio</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e157">Virtutes, quibus recte vivitur, magna bona sunt;
              species autem quorumlibet corporum, sine quibus recte vivi potest, minima bona sunt;
              potentiae vero animae, sine quibus recte vivi non potest, media bona sunt. Virtutibus
              nemo male utitur; caeteris autem bonis, id est, mediis et minimis, non solum bene, sed
              etiam male quisque uti potest.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e165">Augustinus,
              <title>de octoginta tribus quaestionibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e173">Omnis ordinatio, quae virtus etiam nominatur,
              est fruendis frui, et utendis uti.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e180">Isidorus,
              <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e188">Prius vitia extirpanda sunt in homine; deinde
              inserendae virtutes. Nam cohaerere et conjungi non potest veritas cum mendacio, pudor
              cum petulantia, fides cum perfidia, castitas cum luxuria.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e195">Isidorus,
              <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e203">Quisquis ex deteriori jam melior esse coepit,
              caveat de acceptis extolli virtutibus, ne gravius per vanam gloriam corruat, quam
              prius ex lapsu vitiorum jacebat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e210">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Joannem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e218">Sicut malitia, etiam ante gehennam, eos, qui hic
              eam participant, cruciare consuevit, ita virtus etiam ante regnum eos, qui hic eam
              operantur, praeparat voluptati, et cum spe optima et delectatione perpetua vivere
              facit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e225">Ambrosius,
              <title>super Lucam</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e233">Non est virtus non posse peccare, sed nolle,
              atque ita tenere perseverantiam voluntatis, ut voluntas infantiam, usus imitetur
              naturam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e245" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e240">Bernardus, super
            Cantica</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e245">Medium vitiorum virtus tenet, ac proinde sedula
              eget, non solum putatione, sed circumcisione.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e251">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e261" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e253">Bernardus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e261">Virtus in pace acquiritur, in pressura probatur,
              in victoria approbatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e266">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e276" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e268">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e276">Virtus non aliud est, quam recta ratio.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e281">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e291" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e283">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e291">Cum virtus utique medium et modus sit, aeque
              peccatum est quod excedit, sicut quod deficit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e296">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e306" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e298">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e306">Nulli praeclusa est virtus; omnibus patet, omnes
              invitat, omnes admittit; non eligit parentelam, non eligit domum, non censum, nudo
              homine contenta est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e311">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e321" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e313">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e321">Virtus extollit hominem, et super omnia
              mortalibus chara collocat eum; nec ea, quae bona sunt, nec ea, quae mala vocantur, aut
              cupit nimis, aut expavescit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e326">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e336" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e328">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e336">Omnia ista, in quae dominium casus et fortuna
              exercet, servilia sunt; pecunia, et corpus, et honores, imbecilla, fluida, mortalia;
              possessiones incertae: illa rursus, quae virtutis sunt, libera sunt, et
              invicta.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e342">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e352" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e344">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e352">Quemadmodum minuta lumina claritas solis
              obscurat, sic dolores, et molestias, ас injurias, virtus magnitudine sua elidit atque
              opprimit; et quocumque affulsit, ibi quidquid sine ea apparet, extinguitur. Nam non
              magis ullam portionem habent incommoda, cum in virtute inciderunt, quam in mari
              nimbus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e357">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e367" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e359">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e367">Sola virtus praestat gaudium perpetuum, securum:
              etiam si quid obstat, nubium modo intervenit, quae infra feruntur, nec unquam vincunt
              diem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-d1e372">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e382" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Rd1e374">Tullius, in
              <title>Rhetoricis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e18603-Qd1e382">Virtus est animi habitus, naturae modo, rationi
              consentaneus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
